-- Somali Pirates Increase Hijackings of Vessels in First Nine Months of 2010
-- B y   S t u a r t   W a l l a c e
-- 2010-10-18T05:37:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/somali-pirates-increase-hijackings-of-vessels-in-first-nine-months-of-2010.html
Somali pirates accounted for 35 of
39 ship hiackings made globally in the first nine months of the
year, the International Maritime Bureau said in a report.  The total figure was up from 34 made in the same period
last year, the IMB said in the report. A total of 128 ships were
boarded, one crew member was killed, 27 injured and 773 people
taken hostage, the IMB said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stuart Wallace at 
 swallace6@bloomberg.net  